    {
      "content": "Q:  Can my users register their own password reset data?",
      "pos": [
        1544,
        1600
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>A:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Yes, as long as password reset is enabled and they are licensed, they can go to the Password Reset Registration portal at http://aka.ms/ssprsetup to register their authentication information to be used with password reset.",
      "pos": [
        1608,
        1837
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Users can also register by going to the access panel at http://myapps.microsoft.com, clicking the profile tab, and clicking the Register for Password Reset option.",
      "pos": [
        1838,
        2001
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Learn more about how to get your users configured for password reset by reading How to get users configured for password reset.",
      "pos": [
        2002,
        2129
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Q:  Can I define password reset data on behalf of my users?",
      "pos": [
        2137,
        2196
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>A:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Yes, you can do so with DirSync or PowerShell, or through the <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Azure Management Portal<ept id=\"p2\">](https://manage.windowsazure.com)</ept> or Office Admin portal.",
      "pos": [
        2204,
        2355
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Learn more about this feature on the blog post Improved Privacy for Azure AD MFA and Password Reset Phone Numbers and by reading Learn how data is used by password reset.",
      "pos": [
        2356,
        2526
      ]
    },
    {
